{"word":"ὑπειδόμην","slug":"ὑπειδόμην","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑπειδόμην</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>aor2 <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a>\n<el>(<a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>-ιδέσθαι</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to view from below, to behold</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to mistrust, suspect</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:— <el>ὑφοράω</el> is used as <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a><p/></div>"}]}